any’s core values of integrity service value health and safety respect and collaboration and corporate citizenship so that we can provide quality service and value to all of these groups our commitment to our employees is evident as we have been named a top workplace in the bay area for five years in a row and certified as a great place to work® and cal water was ranked “highest in customer satisfaction among water utilities in the west” by jd power in its inaugural water utility satisfaction study life at california water service group we value innovation a positive attitude high ethics and the willingness to learn be part of a team and become a leader in the water industry our hiring strategy enables us to hire retain and develop those with high potential to become leaders of our organization enjoy a work environment that supports your career goals through professional and leadership development and continuing education opportunities employees also gain superior experience in business process improvement through our customized continuous improvement program where employees at all levels work in teams to identify opportunities to improve efficiency or service in addition to learning valuable analytical public speaking and teambuilding skills the program gives employees the opportunity to improve the way we do business check out our job openings today what our employees are saying “i am valued for my experience and hard work my supervisor appreciates my input and works with whatever needs or circumstances arise” — twp employee survey  “i work for a company that actually cares about our customers and is willing to do whatever it takes to provide a high level of service” — twp employee survey  “i feel part of a team and what we do is very important – delivering safe and reliable drinking water i enjoy being a part of a company that encourages community involvement and personal growth” — twp employee survey  “cal water has provided for my family and me for many years and there is simply no better place to work every employee at cal water has an opportunity to grow and advance within the company everything i have i owe to cal water and i’m truly blesses to be an employee” — twp employee survey  httpwwwcalwatergroupcomwpcontentuploadscalwatertestimonialsmp our employees enjoy a generous benefits package we are committed to the health and wellbeing of our employees and their families we offer all eligible employees and their dependents access to comprehensive medical prescription drug dental and vision coverage additional employee benefits include competitive salaries promotions from within k companyfunded pension plan paid holidays and personal days vacation sick leave life insurance life assistance program disability benefits tuition reimbursement other discount programs we support veterans value diversity and provide reasonable accommodations your previous military experience may present new opportunities in the water and wastewater industry we offer challenging careers in a variety of fields and locations throughout california hawaii new mexico and washington the skills and experience you gained in the military may align with duties performed within the company our equal opportunity policy is based upon the philosophy that all people should be treated fairly and with dignity at california water service group and our subsidiaries we do not discriminate against any applicant or employee because of race color religion sex national origin protected veteran status sexual orientation gender identity individuals with disabilities or any other protected class we make all employment decisions in a nondiscriminatory manner we also make reasonable accommodations to meet the special needs of qualified disabled individuals if you require reasonable accommodations please contact the talent acquisition manager in human resources at   candidates who are interested in pursuing a career with california water service group and our subsidiaries sho